{
  "_meta": {
    "service": "matins",
    "description": "Matins (Orthros) — the major morning service. Served daily; most elaborate on Sundays and great feasts. This skeleton covers the full Sunday/festal form; weekday variations noted in conditions.",
    "source": "OCA Typikon / Russian Typikon practice",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "notes": [
      "At All-Night Vigil, Matins follows Vespers directly (no opening prayers).",
      "Weekday Matins omits Polyeleios, Evlogitaria, Gospel, Lauds stichera, and uses read (small) Doxology instead of sung (great) Doxology.",
      "Lenten weekday Matins replaces 'God is the Lord' with 'Alleluia' and adds Lenten troparia.",
      "The Canon (Ode 1–9) is the most complex variable section — initially represented as a single placeholder block."
    ]
  },

  "sections": [

